SS%20Ohio%20missile%20submarine%20in%20a%20dry%20dock%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62d473b1aac2aa0018cb8a6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221302%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUSS%20Ohio%2C%20along%20with%20three%20other%20vessels%20in%20the%20class%2C%20were%20converted%20into%20SSGNs.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-sending-powerful-submarine-middle-east-loud-warning-to-iran-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOhio-class%20submarines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20built%20by%20General%20Dynamics'%20Electric%20Boat%20division%2C%20were%20originally%20a%20force%20of%2018%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic%20missile%20vessels%20first%20commissioned%20in%201981%20with%20a%20sole%20mission%20of%20the%20highest%20stakes%3A%20carrying%20missiles%20with%20nuclear%20warheads.%20In%20the%202000s%2C%20the%20Navy%20converted%20four%20of%20them%20into%20cruise-missile%20submarines%2C%20ending%20their%20role%20in%20the%20nuclear%20forces%20and%20turning%20them%20into%20the%20US%20fleet's%20most%20stealthy%20and%20numerous%20missile%20shooters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20they're%20now%2040%20years%20old%2C%20these%20capable%20submarines%20are%20some%20of%20the%20quietest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20Bryan%20Clark%2C%20a%20retired%20Navy%20submarine%20officer%20and%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20in%20large%20part%20because%20of%20their%20size%2C%20which%20allows%20for%20substantial%20dampening%20and%20sound%20silencing%20equipment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20well%20as%20their%20aggressive%20maintenance%20program.%20Each%20SSGN%20carries%20154%20Tomahawk%20missiles%20and%20can%20carry%20about%20two%20dozen%20special%20operators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESSGN%20is%20an%20abbreviation%20for%20%26quot%3Bsubsurface%20guided%20nuclear%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20SS%20